What is the common academic approach of defining a measure of risk and a measure of gain?

Possible Answers

YES       Risk is defined as standard deviation and gain is defined as mean return
Academically, risk and gain are defined as standard deviation and mean return. In practice, many other measures of risk and gain are also used!

Risk is defined as mean return and gain is defined as mean return


Risk is defined as mean return and gain is defined as portfolio variance
